<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-17T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-17T22:00:00-05:00" n="1158" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1158">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Manhard, Philip W.: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-18T11:00:00+08:00">March 18
                                        [<hi rend="italic">17?</hi>], 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received March 17—11:56 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Unnumbered. Re Contel 296, March 16 [<hi rend="italic">17?</hi>].<note n="30" xml:id="d1158fn30">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> Manhard and Armstrong applied
                            March 17 Public Safety Bureau for permission proceed Mukden. Informed
                            reply would be made in due course.</p>
                        <p>Deptel 80, February 16 and Embtel 55, February 18<note n="31" xml:id="d1158fn31">Latter is the same as telegram No. 412 from the
                                Ambassador in China, <ref target="#pg_937">p. 937</ref>.</note>
                            noting impossibility [<hi rend="italic">improbability</hi>] early
                            assignment, does Department’s authorization send Chinese messenger still
                            hold?</p>
                        <p>Sent Department; repeated Shanghai 300, for info Nanking, OffEmb
                            Canton.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>